    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Art or architectural elements that are associated with urban design, planning, and preservation of a city, town, or district. For art having the purpose of beautifying and enriching public places, but not necessarily located in a city or associated with urban design, use "public art." For art created in urban environments, but not necessarily sanctioned or legally displayed, prefer "urban art."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079228/Grove Art Online (2008-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Kunst of architecturale elementen die verband houden met stadsontwerp en -planning en het behoud van een stad of wijk. Gebruik 'openbare kunst' voor kunst die tot doel heeft om openbare plekken mooier te maken of te verrijken, maar die niet noodzakelijk in een stad hoeft te zijn of verbonden is met stadsontwerp. Gebruik 'urban art' voor kunst in stedelijke omgevingen die niet noodzakelijk gesanctioneerd of legaal tentoongesteld is.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109894/UvA Talen</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Elementos artísticos ou arquitetônicos associados ao desenho urbano, planejamento e preservação de uma cidade, vila ou distrito. Para a arte que tem como objetivo embelezar e enriquecer locais públicos, mas não necessariamente localizada em uma cidade ou associada ao desenho urbano, utilize “arte pública”. Para arte criada em ambientes urbanos, mas não necessariamente sancionada ou exibida legalmente, prefira "arte urbana</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
